Dockerfile integration for the SM121 sgl-kernel source patch.

Two structural changes to container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly:

1. Add `patch` to the apt-get install list in the builder stage.
   The base image (scitrera/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev) does not ship the
   `patch` binary, and we need it to apply sgl-kernel-sm121.patch.

2. MOVE the sglang Python package install (`uv pip install ./python`) and
   the COPY + apply of sgl-kernel-sm121.patch to the END of the builder
   stage, right before stages/directory_split2.sh runs.

   Why: our patch target `python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh`
   is a JIT header (compiled at runtime via nvrtc, not during the Docker
   build). It only needs to be present in the installed sglang Python
   package -- the expensive `sgl-kernel` C++ build earlier in the Dockerfile
   never reads it. By placing the patch LATE (after sgl-kernel build,
   flashinfer install, transformers install etc.), iterating on the patch
   content no longer invalidates those expensive layers. Rebuild after a
   patch change drops from ~40-60 min to ~2-3 min.

   This deletes the existing `uv pip install ./python` block near line 98
   and re-inserts it (together with the patch COPY + apply) near line 188.

Idempotency: `patch --dry-run` runs before the real apply -- if the
upstream file drifts such that the hunks no longer match, the build
fails immediately with a clear diagnostic instead of producing an
unpatched image. `grep -q 'StageCount<1>'` after apply confirms the
replacement landed.

Apply to: container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly in the local
clone of scitrera/cuda-containers. The sm121 branch in that clone
carries this patch; see scripts/build_sm121_image.sh.

--- a/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
+++ b/container-build/Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@
         python3-pip \
         python3-dev \
         git \
+        patch \
         wget \
         ccache \
         libcudnn9-cuda-13 \
@@ -95,10 +96,6 @@
 ENV SETUPTOOLS_SCM_PRETEND_VERSION_FOR_SGLANG=${SGLANG_VERSION} \
     SETUPTOOLS_SCM_PRETEND_VERSION=${SGLANG_VERSION}
 
-# Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch)
-RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
-    uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python
-
 # Copy any pre-built sgl-kernel wheels from build context (may be empty)
 COPY wheel-cache/ /data/wheel-cache/
 
@@ -185,6 +182,31 @@
         uv pip install -U transformers --pre; \
     fi
 
+# SM121 (DGX Spark GB10) shared memory fix for cutlass_moe_fp4.
+# Patches run_fp4_blockwise_scaled_group_mm_sm120() in the JIT-compiled
+# nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh to use StageCount<1> + non-pingpong schedule,
+# cutting mainloop SMEM from 102400 B (100 KiB) to below the 101376 B
+# (99 KiB) SM121 budget. See patches/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch header and
+# NVIDIA/cutlass#3144 for the verified SMEM numbers and root cause.
+#
+# Placed LATE in the builder stage (after sgl-kernel build + flashinfer +
+# transformers install) so that iterating on the patch content does not
+# invalidate the expensive sgl-kernel build layer. The .cuh is a JIT
+# header compiled via nvrtc at runtime, so it only needs to be present
+# in the installed sglang Python package, not in the sgl-kernel C++ build.
+COPY patches/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch
+RUN set -e; cd /data/sglang && \
+    patch --dry-run -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch && \
+    patch -p1 < /tmp/sgl-kernel-sm121.patch && \
+    grep -q 'StageCount<1>' python/sglang/jit_kernel/csrc/moe/nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh && \
+    echo 'SM121 sgl-kernel patch applied successfully'
+
+# Install sglang package (no deps, no build isolation since base has torch).
+# Moved here from its original location (~line 98) so that the installed
+# dist-packages picks up the patched nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh above.
+RUN --mount=type=cache,id=uv-cache,target=/root/.cache/uv \
+    uv pip install --no-build-isolation --no-deps ./python
+
 # Break up dist-packages into smaller layers to avoid hitting Docker layer size limits
 COPY stages/directory_split2.sh /opt/directory_split2.sh
 RUN chmod +x /opt/directory_split2.sh && \
